A '''clothing bin''' is a container in which clothing is placed to be donated to charity organizations (e.g., the [[Salvation Army]]) or for recyling in other ways. They are typically provided by the charities themselves or by local authorities. 

Unsuitable materials are sometimes placed in the bins. These are costly for the organizations concerned to dispose of, and this misuse has at times lead to bins being withdrawn.

